The paper deals with the static analysis of concurrent systems, specifically negotiation diagrams, which are a model of concurrent computation. This falls under the category of Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of various analysis problems, which suggests a connection to Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper deals with software engineering issues such as detecting anti-patterns, which suggests a connection to Software Engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the use of Petri nets, which are a common tool in Programming Languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms for computing summaries and expected costs, which suggests a connection to Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
